[5] Pakistan (Punjab)
Date: Sun 28 Jul 2013
Source: Pakistan Today, Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) report [edited]
http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2013/07/27/city/lahore/immunisation-drive-halves-measles-cases-in-punjab/


Extended Programme for Immunisation's (EMI) Dr Younas has claimed a decrease of over 50 per cent in measles cases in Punjab [province]. On Saturday [27 Jul 2013], he said that an intensive drive had resulted in the reduction of daily measles cases from 50-80 to just 20-40. He claimed that the figures would continue to improve as time progressed, as the measles [vaccine recipients] would start developing [immunity] 3 weeks [after] their initial vaccination. During the anti-measles drive from [29 Apr 2013] to [5 May 2013], around 250 000 children ranging from 6 months to 10 years old were vaccinated.

Moreover, only 27 cases of measles were reported in Punjab [province] during the last 24 hours, including only 3 from Lahore. However, the total cases of measles during the previous 6-and-a-half months were 22 885, including 192 deaths in Punjab [province].

